\textbf{Use lm() to discover and separate variables and compartmentalize
them into fewer (but still powerful) variables. The data should remove
all NA values by replacing them with the median values of the variable.
The compartments should be akin to Skill(physical attributes, talents),
Efficiency(ratings, grades), Production(total contributions),
Expectation(ADP, draft pick, appearances), and Situation. These fewer
variables should allow for a model to reasonably predict future fantasy
points without having to deal with NA values and extreme skewness of
having too many variables.}
